Brazil great, Kaka, has predicted Real Madrid’s Champions League final against Liverpool. Real Madrid will face Liverpool in the Champions League final on May 28 in Paris. The Los Blancos had eliminated Manchester City in the semi-final, while Jurgen Klopp’s side had knocked Villarreal out of the tournament. But Kaka has now backed Carlo Ancelotti’s side to beat the Premier League giants. “What a great season Real Madrid is having. Carlo Ancelotti is there as well. I am very happy with this year. Now we will see in Paris what is going to happen, but I hope Real Madrid can win another final,” Kaka told Sky Sports. He added, “Liverpool is playing really, really well. They’ve been playing together for many, many years. They’ve a lot of good players that can decide the game in every moment. The game will be really amazing and also the fact that they lost the last final against Real Madrid. “There is a few ingredients for this final that makes for a special game.”